headline: UPS Q1 Earnings Call: Strategic Network Overhaul and Tariff Uncertainty Shape Outlook
summary: Parcel delivery company UPS (NYSE:UPS) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $21.55 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.49 per share was 8.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
